28
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:58,390
 Let the hunt begin. 

29
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:17,900
   

30
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,910
 A Level Six Demon Beast? 

31
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:40,720
 Take the strike of my sword first! 

32
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:53,330
 You're quite capable. 

33
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,900
 Again! 

34
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:30,311
 Four Symbols: Black Tortoise Array! 

35
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,410
 Go! 

36
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:46,510
 The purity of the color is not bad. 

37
00:03:46,510 --> 00:03:48,050
   

38
00:03:48,050 --> 00:03:52,030
 They say that time stands still in the mountains 

39
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:54,860
 while a thousand years pass in the mortal world. 

40
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:56,560
 My story 
   

41
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,950
 starts from 200 years ago. 
   

42
00:03:58,950 --> 00:04:00,950
Older Brother, wake up.

43
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:03,940
Mother baked pancakes and wants you to go home now. 
    

44
00:04:05,650 --> 00:04:06,770
Pancakes?

45
00:04:06,770 --> 00:04:07,930
Where did she get the flour?

46
00:04:07,930 --> 00:04:09,530
 Father borrowed flour from Sixth Uncle and Aunt Zheng. 

47
00:04:09,530 --> 00:04:12,770
 I don't think anyone will believe me 

48
00:04:12,770 --> 00:04:15,030
 that I stepped into the world of cultivation 

49
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:17,690
 because of a pancake and three bowls of flour. 

50
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,070
- This is big. 
 - Here.

51
00:04:19,070 --> 00:04:21,600
 The Han family of Wuligou Village, Qingniu Town... 
   

52
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,205
 had been farmers for generations. 

53
00:04:24,205 --> 00:04:27,392
 Third Uncle was the only one who became an outer disciple of the Seven Mystics Sect. 

54
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:29,906
 He became the most respected man in the village. 
   

55
00:04:29,906 --> 00:04:32,080
Didn't you and Old Uncle Zhang give him an excellent name?

56
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:35,085
 For a village boy like me, 

57
00:04:35,085 --> 00:04:36,580
 getting into the Seven Mystics Sect 

58
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:39,080
 was my only opportunity to change my family's fate. 

59
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,020
Han Li?

60
00:04:40,020 --> 00:04:41,210
That's right. Han Li.

61
00:04:41,210 --> 00:04:44,630
 This chubby boy is Zhang Tie. 

62
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:47,260
 He's my best friend in the village. 

63
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:49,430
Eating pancakes? 
    

64
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:51,510
- I have some, too. 
 - You, too?

65
00:04:51,510 --> 00:04:52,752
- Not bad at all. 
 - My father made these for me...

66
00:04:52,752 --> 00:04:54,180
after borrowing three bowls of flour from Uncle Niu.

67
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:55,420
He forbade me from eating them now.

68
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:57,140
 According to the village rules, 

69
00:04:57,140 --> 00:04:59,750
 before setting out on a long journey or doing something important, 

70
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:02,140
 we must eat white flour pancakes 
   

71
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:03,340
 even if we have to borrow the flour. 

72
00:05:03,340 --> 00:05:06,760
- If Blockhead gets in, we don't need to return the flour. 
  - However, 

73
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:08,300
 - whatever we borrowed...  
 - You can eat first.

74
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:09,930
 must be returned. 

75
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:12,750
 That's also one of the rules. 

76
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:17,760
 Back then, I thought about the three bowls of flour... 

77
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:18,740
My older brother has a new name now.

78
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:20,800
 - those people in front of me...  
 - What's his new name?

79
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,050
 - I must get into Seven Mystics Sect.  
 - Han Li.

80
00:05:22,050 --> 00:05:23,632
"Li," as in "erecting" a tombstone"?

81
00:05:23,632 --> 00:05:26,420
Your family is erecting a tombstone instead.

82
00:05:26,420 --> 00:05:29,900
"Li" in Han Li as in "Standing upright between Heaven and Earth". 
    

83
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:32,312
Han Li...

84
00:05:32,312 --> 00:05:35,530
 By the way, I have an official name now. 

85
00:05:35,530 --> 00:05:37,580
 I'm no longer Blockhead. 

86
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:39,580
 My name is Han Li. 

87
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:41,900
 "Li," as in "Standing upright between Heaven and Earth". 

88
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:46,150
   

89
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:48,400
This year's entrance test is a mountain hike.

90
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,460
The first seven participants to reach the peak will join the sect.

91
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:52,540
The rest will go home.

92
00:05:58,746 --> 00:06:00,170
Stop.

93
00:06:00,170 --> 00:06:01,430
That's enough.

94
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:03,140
The first seven participants have been decided.

95
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:06,802
The rest of you didn't make it. 
    

96
00:06:06,802 --> 00:06:08,290
Go back.

97
00:06:08,290 --> 00:06:10,310
 We failed? How can I return the flour then? 

98
00:06:10,310 --> 00:06:13,280
Senior Brother, no. Don't!

99
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:15,480
- Zhang Tie! 
 - You shouldn't have eaten that much.

100
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,460
Do you know?

101
00:06:16,460 --> 00:06:20,870
You wouldn't have been in ninth place if you had eaten less.

102
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:24,415
I... So that makes me number eight, then.

103
00:06:24,415 --> 00:06:26,085
Senior Brother!

104
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,290
- Tie! 
 - Still putting on an act?

105
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:30,920
- What's wrong? 
 - He's really sick. It's not an act!

106
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,380
Tie! Are you all right?

107
00:06:32,380 --> 00:06:33,770
Where does it hurt?

108
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:35,380
Physician Mo.

109
00:06:39,580 --> 00:06:41,150
Han Li!

110
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:46,090
Just look at him.

111
00:06:46,090 --> 00:06:48,390
He ate too many pancakes before the mountain hike.

112
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:49,460
He ate three.

113
00:06:49,460 --> 00:06:51,260
He was hiking in the cold as well. 
    

114
00:06:51,260 --> 00:06:53,510
Does he have a death wish?

115
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:03,940
You're fine now.

116
00:07:03,940 --> 00:07:05,210
You're considered lucky.

117
00:07:05,210 --> 00:07:08,330
Physician Mo is the savior of Sect Leader Wang of the Seven Mystics Sect.

118
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:09,570
He's the divine healer.

119
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:10,741
Still not thanking him?

120
00:07:10,741 --> 00:07:13,043
Thank you, Physician Mo! Thank you for saving me!

121
00:07:13,043 --> 00:07:15,235
- Thank you, Physician Mo! 
 - Physician Mo.

122
00:07:15,235 --> 00:07:17,136
Are you here to select those who failed the test?

123
00:07:17,136 --> 00:07:19,726
You're asking the obvious.

124
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:22,390
What do you think about them?

125
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:26,270
I'll take these two.

126
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:29,860
Come with me.

127
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:44,840
   

128
00:07:49,834 --> 00:07:51,904
 This place is beautiful. 

129
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:56,700
This is Shenshou Valley.

130
00:07:56,700 --> 00:08:01,820
Sect Leader Wang of the Seven Mystics Sect specially gifted it to me.

131
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:04,850
I saved his life back then.

132
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:07,210
Blockhead,

133
00:08:07,210 --> 00:08:09,710
I suppose this is our home now.

134
00:08:10,810 --> 00:08:14,010
It depends on whether you two have good fortune.

135
00:08:33,090 --> 00:08:36,020
Do you recognize what's written on the wall?

136
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:41,622
   

137
00:08:41,622 --> 00:08:43,660
We don't.

138
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:47,770
   

139
00:08:47,770 --> 00:08:48,997
Are you both illiterate?

140
00:08:48,997 --> 00:08:50,915
Yes.

141
00:08:50,915 --> 00:08:53,036
What can you both do then?

142
00:08:53,036 --> 00:08:55,092
- Master, we know how to grow crops. 
 - Don't call me Master.

143
00:08:55,092 --> 00:08:57,243
I haven't decided to accept you both as my disciples.

144
00:08:57,243 --> 00:09:02,284
It depends on your performance whether you both can stay.

145
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:11,070
Sit down.

146
00:09:18,076 --> 00:09:19,348
Silly kids.

147
00:09:19,348 --> 00:09:22,699
There's no such thing as a free lunch in the world.

148
00:09:22,699 --> 00:09:25,220
This is a three-legged stool.

149
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:30,930
If you wish to serve me, you must be careful at all times.

150
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:38,900
What is that smell?

151
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,580
Did you bathe?

152
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:12,640
Han Li, why do I feel giddy?

153
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:18,060
What's wrong with the water...

154
00:10:52,050 --> 00:10:53,570
Zhang Tie, wake up.

155
00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:55,060
Wake up.

156
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:00,690
You are young indeed.

157
00:11:00,690 --> 00:11:02,540
You regained consciousness rather fast.

158
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:04,650
What did you add in the water?

159
00:11:04,650 --> 00:11:06,180
Immortal Grass Dew.

160
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:07,460
It gets rid of stench.

161
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:09,370
Take a sniff at yourselves

162
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:11,160
and check if you still smell.

163
00:11:13,857 --> 00:11:18,820
It wasn't sweat on your bodies.

164
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:20,200
It was stench.

165
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,680
The stench of a mortal.

166
00:11:23,126 --> 00:11:25,210
Stench of a mortal?

167
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:27,280
Mortals consume grains.

168
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:28,920
They can't absorb the essence of Heaven and Earth.

169
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,970
They gather all the impurities in their bodies instead.

170
00:11:30,970 --> 00:11:33,300
Of course, they stink.

171
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:36,720
Don't you two feel any different?

172
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,780
Don't you guys feel spirited and refreshed?

173
00:11:41,669 --> 00:11:44,660
Blockhead, I really think I smell nice now.

174
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:46,781
My head doesn't feel heavy anymore.

175
00:11:47,970 --> 00:11:50,370
 I seem to feel much better now. 

176
00:12:00,180 --> 00:12:05,090
Brat, at first glance, I could tell you came with a motive.

177
00:12:05,090 --> 00:12:07,250
 Was it that obvious? 

178
00:12:07,690 --> 00:12:10,820
I don't care about your motive when you're here.

179
00:12:10,820 --> 00:12:15,900
I can save you or destroy you with just a lift of my fingers.

180
00:12:17,389 --> 00:12:19,979
Want to give it a try if you don't believe me?

181
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:27,440
 This won't do. He'll chase me away if I keep this up. 

182
00:12:32,011 --> 00:12:33,370
Physician Mo, thank you for taking us in.

183
00:12:33,370 --> 00:12:34,770
You're our savior.

184
00:12:34,770 --> 00:12:36,420
We will obey you in the future.

185
00:12:36,420 --> 00:12:38,470
We won't upset you.

186
00:12:42,460 --> 00:12:44,700
Don't be scared.

187
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:52,840
I scared you both to let you know who establishes the rules here.

188
00:12:54,370 --> 00:12:56,900
I only have three rules.

189
00:12:56,900 --> 00:13:03,010
First rule: You must be mindful of every matter in this valley.

190
00:13:05,860 --> 00:13:09,340
Second rule: Don't make contact with those fools outside.

191
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:11,200
Third rule:

192
00:13:12,330 --> 00:13:15,361
It's also the most important rule.

193
00:13:15,361 --> 00:13:18,720
I'll teach you a chant.

194
00:13:19,288 --> 00:13:21,700
You must always practice it.

195
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:24,050
Don't be lazy.

196
00:13:24,050 --> 00:13:26,670
If you can't follow these three rules,

197
00:13:26,670 --> 00:13:29,100
you'd better scram and don't waste my time.

198
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,790
I'll remember that.

199
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:34,810
You accepted this rather fast.

200
00:13:34,810 --> 00:13:36,240
Excellent.

201
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:39,930
I'll see how you keep your promise.

202
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,960
There are only three of us but there are six dishes.

203
00:14:11,290 --> 00:14:13,120
Physician Mo.

204
00:14:14,138 --> 00:14:16,450
I'm not hungry.

205
00:14:16,450 --> 00:14:18,260
I will watch you eat.

206
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:20,101
How can we do this?

207
00:14:20,101 --> 00:14:22,531
Of course, you must pick up your chopsticks first.

208
00:14:29,770 --> 00:14:31,650
Sit down.

209
00:14:34,650 --> 00:14:36,630
Pick up your chopsticks.

210
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:39,500
Eat.

211
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:44,380
From tomorrow on, you two will serve me.

212
00:14:44,380 --> 00:14:47,320
Don't let me take care of you again.

213
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,550
What meat is this?

214
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:49,641
It tastes really good.

215
00:14:49,641 --> 00:14:51,140
That's not meat.

216
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:52,620
It's the root of Chinese cedar.

217
00:14:52,620 --> 00:14:54,530
What's that? Is it the root of a tree?

218
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:57,670
Chinese cedar has a firm and upright structure.

219
00:14:57,670 --> 00:15:01,340
It's good for hair and skin in traditional medicine.

220
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:05,100
After it's harvested, mix it with raw scallions and steam it thoroughly.

221
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:08,530
Steam for half a day, shred it finely,

222
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:12,000
and hang it in the south corner of the house to dry.

223
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,045
Drizzle sesame oil on it

224
00:15:14,045 --> 00:15:16,100
and it can be used as a filling.

225
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:19,440
I thought tree roots were only eaten during famine.

226
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:22,740
You eat to fill your stomach.

227
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:26,750
I eat to cultivate.

228
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:28,380
 Cultivate? 

229
00:15:28,380 --> 00:15:30,900
Rest immediately after finishing your meal.

230
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:32,900
Don't forget to wake up tomorrow morning

231
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:36,160
when the rooster crows. Take a bath and light the incense.

232
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:41,110
Get ready to learn the chant.

233
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:48,450
 What kind of chant? 

234
00:15:48,450 --> 00:15:50,430
 Why do we need to bathe and light the incense? 

235
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:01,150
 You still have time to prepare bathwater and cook for them? 

236
00:16:01,150 --> 00:16:02,630
 Hurry and teach them the chant. 

237
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:04,360
 Check if they have spiritual roots. 

238
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,200
 Don't get me blockheads again! 

239
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:09,000
Fine... All right.

240
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:12,590
Go away. Go away!

241
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,972
- Good morning, Physician Mo. 
 - Time to wake up.

242
00:16:29,972 --> 00:16:31,730
The sun is shining on your backsides.

243
00:16:31,730 --> 00:16:34,190
We just finished bathing and changing our clothes.

244
00:16:38,770 --> 00:16:42,450
The chant is divided into several levels.

245
00:16:42,450 --> 00:16:47,810
If you can master Level One in the next three months,

246
00:16:47,810 --> 00:16:51,050
you can officially pay respect to me as your master.

247
00:16:51,050 --> 00:16:54,400
After that, just like the disciples of the Seven Mystics Sect,

248
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:56,361
you'll also receive a silver each month.

249
00:16:56,361 --> 00:16:58,431
There's actually money?

250
00:16:59,148 --> 00:17:02,900
I spent a lot of effort obtaining this chant.

251
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:06,570
I won't spare you if you dare to tell anyone else about it.

252
00:17:06,570 --> 00:17:07,860
Understand?

253
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:09,570
We won't tell anyone else about it! We won't.

254
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:13,450
Since you are illiterate, just repeat my chant.

255
00:17:13,450 --> 00:17:15,845
Attain ultimate emptiness.

256
00:17:15,845 --> 00:17:18,872
Attain ultimate weirdness.

257
00:17:18,872 --> 00:17:21,530
This is driving me crazy.

258
00:17:21,530 --> 00:17:23,973
- Emptiness! 
 - Emptiness.

259
00:17:23,973 --> 00:17:25,380
You're really annoying me.

260
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:26,860
Unbelievable.

261
00:17:26,860 --> 00:17:29,540
- Maintain. 
 - Maintain.

262
